==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''batting average'''
#{{Cricket}} A [[statistical]] [[estimation]] of the [[scoring]] [[ability]] of a [[batsman]]; equal to the [[total]] [[number]] of [[run]]s scored [[divide]]d by the number of times [[out]].
#{{Baseball}} A [[statistical]] [[estimation]] of the hitting [[ability]] of a [[batter]]; equal to the  [[number]] of [[hit]]s [[divide]]d by the number of official [[at-bat]]s.  Normally expressed as a real number instead of an average despite the name.
#: ''Jones has a .279 '''batting average'''.''